    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I take the earliest<lb/> opportunity to forward to you a<lb/> copy
                of the report &amp; proceedings<lb/> of the adjourned anniversary meeting<lb/> of
                the H. H. B. Society held on<lb/>
                <date>Sunday the 7th of November</date> &amp; at which<lb/> a resolution was passed
                to the effect<lb/> that the proceedings of the meeting<lb/> should be sent to the
                Occident<lb/> for publication as usual. At the<lb/> same time I am requested by
                the<lb/> President &amp; several members of the<lb/> Board to express their regret
                that<lb/> the customary courtesy &amp; attention<lb/> due to you as a minister &amp;
                friend<lb/> of the poor was unintentionally<lb/> omitted, I was not aware that</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>others than members received<lb/> invitations or notices. Trusting<lb/> that this
                explanation will prove<lb/> satisfactory</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Matilda H. Cohen</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Secr. Pro Tem</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>1828 Rittenhouse Square</placeName>
            </p>
            <p><date>November 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1858</date>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
